# Build Believe Fit — Render static-site routing (_redirects)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Served from dist/ root (Vite copies public/_redirects verbatim). This is the
# routing authority for the React SPA on Render: it bridges legacy monolith URLs
# (the .html pages the old GitHub Pages site served) to the new React routes, then
# falls through to the SPA so client-side React Router handles everything else.
#
# Rule order matters — Render evaluates top-to-bottom, first match wins. The
# catch-all SPA rewrite MUST be last.
#
# ⚠️ The conflicting `routes:` block was removed from render.yaml in the same
# commit so THIS file is the single source of routing truth (render.yaml `routes`
# would otherwise shadow these rules and the legacy 301s would never fire).

# ── Static legal documents — serve the real files (Google Play compliance). ──
# 200 = serve in place (NOT a redirect, NOT the SPA fallback).
/privacy.html        /privacy.html        200
/terms.html          /terms.html          200

# ── Legacy app + admin entry points → the React auth gate. ──
# The old client PWA and admin consoles all funnel into /login now.
/bbf-app.html        /login               301
/admin.html          /login               301
/mastermind-portal.html  /login           301
/coach-lab.html      /login               301
/lab-editor.html     /login               301

# Clean-URL aliases the legacy site used for the app entry.
/app                 /login               301
/portal              /login               301

# ── Legacy marketing / funnel pages → the React marketing landing (/). ──
# These had no distinct React route; their content now lives on the landing
# (e.g. legacy #playbooks == the Positional Blueprints section).
/index.html          /                    301
/sports-hub.html     /                    301
/playbooks.html      /                    301
/busy-parent-transformation.html  /       301

# ── Post-checkout / thank-you pages (no React equivalent yet) → landing. ──
# Avoids a dead-end/black-screen; revisit when dedicated success routes exist.
/payment-success.html  /                  301
/thank-you.html      /                    301
/gracias.html        /                    301
/obrigado.html       /                    301
/thank-you           /                    301
/gracias             /                    301
/obrigado            /                    301

# ── SPA CATCH-ALL — must be the LAST rule. ──
# Any path not matched above is served the React shell; React Router takes over.
/*                   /index.html          200
